<paragraph id="230FE0EA1EAFAF0BC3EBE455EBA4AF82" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="69C2CB1F9BAE8A04C835E02620E822C8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calliandrae">Pilostyles calliandrae</taxonomicName>
(Gardner) R.Br., Trans. Linn. Soc. London 19(3): 247. [6 Nov 1844] = 
<taxonomicName id="7620F0B80E934600097220D20335C2C4" authorityName="Gardn" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Apodanthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="calliandrae">
<emphasis id="30CF0776E5FEE9391F41CDD8FBD77979" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Apodanthes calliandrae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gardner, Icon. Pl. 7: t. 644. 1844 [Jan 1844] = 
<taxonomicName id="A85DCE8A79B7BB98E9D05392E63F41AD" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Frostia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calliandrae">
<emphasis id="FA25E6E966EB03B7A077B82D5BA2BF3B" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Frostia calliandrae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gardner) H. Karst., Nov. Actorum Acad. Caes. Leop.-Carol. Nat. Cur. 26: 921. 1858. Type: Brazil, Amazonas, near Maynas [Manaus], Feb. 1840, 
<emphasis id="0C19E204372EB85D46E98D6B6451D8D2" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">G. Gardner 3639</emphasis>
(K000601222), 
<emphasis id="7A673071143D5CF549021C1FD144D46B" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">syn. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="065CBBE7C215BA80DF18E7432E9B95ED" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="092A68EE91E50B488C7470D70FCA61DA" authorityName="Hook fil" authorityYear="1873" baseAuthorityName="Karst." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caulotreti">Pilostyles caulotreti</taxonomicName>
(Karsten) Hook.f., Prodr. (DC.) 17: 116. 1873 
<emphasis id="03B7D7CD8EB6217DD6A92E174E0A944B" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">= Sarna caulotreti</emphasis>
Karsten, Linnaea 28: 415. Jun 1857 [1856]. Type: Venezuela, 
<emphasis id="E3A7CFDBD5B019DD620EAE6C6E8F3064" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">H. Karsten s.n</emphasis>
. (W, destroyed in WWII). Comment: 
<bibRefCitation id="42061BF9BB4BCB98441EDA7D6FC43FB2" author="Gentry, AH" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" pagination="17 - 21" publicationUrl="10.2307/2394766" refId="B8" refString="Gentry, AH, 1973. Flora of Panama, Part IV. Family 50A. Rafflesiaceae. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 60: 17 - 21, 10.2307/2394766" title="Flora of Panama, Part IV. Family 50 A. Rafflesiaceae." url="10.2307/2394766" volume="60" year="1973">Gentry (1973)</bibRefCitation>
considered this name as synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="F2ADACD63EAA762F9B605E2F7DB80883" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="blanchetii">
<emphasis id="060D96D8DA2A800AEB2D287EE4685B9E" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Pilostyles blanchetii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we agree with this assessment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09D1C862805996E2E8EC5C2D67FE3F09" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="5C95F553C0E9883FC7FB7981272E9DDC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ingae">Pilostyles ingae</taxonomicName>
(Karsten) Hooker f., Prodr. (DC.) 17: 116. 1873 = 
<taxonomicName id="B8B2B1691C1FCC43A6320235EFBD384F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rafflesiaceae" genus="Sarna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ingae">
<emphasis id="D3CF86A4364FFFCFC2AD299FF37142DA" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Sarna ingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
H.Karst., Linnaea 28: 415. Jun 1857 [1856]. Type: Colombia, Cauca, 
<normalizedToken id="FAE3B2D8CBF8C97D3A0B429525ACCF62" originalValue="Popayán">Popayan</normalizedToken>
, parasitic on 
<emphasis id="496EDF00A65E90F17FE2B979F6E2B7E0" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Inga, H. Karsten s.n</emphasis>
. (W, destroyed in WWII), 
<emphasis id="7205EFD8D64E965C13CA60D925A54231" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">syn. nov.</emphasis>
(based on the protologue).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D5C7C741DFF7645C0E22F34BBAD9AF77" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="B2274020256E13DB119B49876089EA75" authorityName="Ule" authorityYear="1915" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galactiae">Pilostyles galactiae</taxonomicName>
Ule, Notizbl. 
<normalizedToken id="0BEF45028F59CE679A52C50778C347B0" originalValue="Königl">Koenigl</normalizedToken>
. Bot. Gart. Berlin 6: 292. 1915. Type: Brazil, Amazonia, Surumu River, tributary of the Rio Branco, Oct. 1909 and Mar. 1910, parasitic on 
<taxonomicName id="6355819E4E9DC113AEEA752269936F25" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Galactia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="jussiaeana">
<emphasis id="C7D3198CAB21671E6C7AA9F5739AFC95" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Galactia jussiaeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kunth., 
<emphasis id="D295A3FDF7A205269508E2F60654CAE4" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">E. Ule 7895</emphasis>
(B, holotype destroyed in WWII; isotype NY), 
<emphasis id="110408F071744287B7806007ADF92C65" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">syn. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3854A10098C0CEF53DD4DDBEC13878F7" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="4FF6107A107F1E655D8C53309CE4BD13" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="goyazensis">Pilostyles goyazensis</taxonomicName>
Ule, Ber. Deutsch. Bot. Ges. 33: 475. 1915. Syntypes (all parasitic on 
<taxonomicName id="96D0A931E7D6135E58433CC991BEB9F4" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="69CE2D52BEAF3629C9F8BFE18776A28D" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Mimosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
): Brazil, Goias, region near city of Corumba, Sobradinho, Aug. 1892, 
<emphasis id="227590C4DE9ABDD803FA0B53321C87ED" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">E. Ule 3097</emphasis>
; Serra dos Pyreneos, Mun. Corumba, Dec. 1892, 
<emphasis id="B03DA08AE2E309C730461D3D2BE4E477" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">E. Ule 3098</emphasis>
; same location, Dec. 1892, 
<emphasis id="4AAF6EAAFA5C3BC37A7D438326D63F54" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">E. Ule 3099</emphasis>
; in the Corumba region, Aug. 1892, not flowering, 
<emphasis id="2F8B10A94241DC18B2D00DB734BACA12" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">E. Ule s.n</emphasis>
.; Serra dos Pyreneos, Aug. 1892, not reproductive, 
<emphasis id="291A32FB78CF075A982C667D659A5D75" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">E. Ule s.n</emphasis>
. (all in B, material destroyed in WWII), 
<emphasis id="90D48FBE42C573B9C4A2251175252D29" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">syn. nov.</emphasis>
(based on the protologue).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ABD1512FFFCA3392CFE71EF38E2F020F" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="EDA63397D6ACF7270DB6C03F1B65C08D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="globosa">Pilostyles globosa</taxonomicName>
(S.Watson ex Robinson) Hemsl., J. Linn. Soc., Bot. 31: 311. 1896 = 
<taxonomicName id="6F30DE6541EA066736B6F32B925C0294" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Apodanthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis id="D2BB29C700C13097763AD43E9E9D759A" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Apodanthes globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
S.Watson ex Robinson., Bot. Gaz. 16: 83, tab. 9, 1891. Type: Mexico, Northern part, Sierra Madre, parasitic on 
<taxonomicName id="E6F589BAAA9E42D4B13426FFEB2E44C0" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bauhinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="lunarioides">
<emphasis id="83D9AB91E90072472117FD556B82C500" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Bauhinia lunarioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A. Gray, 
<emphasis id="5298059A2699F88DA6D05BB513470872" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">C. G. Pringle 1950</emphasis>
(G), 
<emphasis id="36FE84B4EEA89F3D43AF2AEE3A4B2CF6" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">syn. nov.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="032CFED472E9D6851559033FED3C424D" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="729BDA5F4F693556D24D3C6988DD3D55" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stawiarskii">Pilostyles stawiarskii</taxonomicName>
Vattimo-Gil, Revista Brasil. Biol. 10: 196. 1950. Type: Brazil, 
<normalizedToken id="7E650DA0E78178410D4AA0D27611D6F6" originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
, Mun. de Palmas, parasitic on 
<taxonomicName id="E0995550C4A19D831D69CBC93B9A2F94" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="scabrella">
<emphasis id="D2E7C87913C8157A3ACB540AB5950314" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Mimosa scabrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Benth. [incl. its synonym 
<taxonomicName id="4805D568077205ED6ED902710FF530FD" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="bracaatinga">
<emphasis id="CE9D6014045A90B9982F4B28F7503F7E" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Mimosa bracaatinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hoehne], Jan. 1948 and Feb. 1948, 
<emphasis id="C007D64C3686A733D788CF5CF4FC0595" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">V. Stawiarski</emphasis>
R50.591 and 50.592 (R, photos). There is also a topotypical collection from Dec. 1949, 
<emphasis id="3077ECDAA68C85F76EFF4F5F10BE4BF6" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">syn. nov.</emphasis>
(based on the protologue).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B260F555E11DFF61E27DECE9161FDF2" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="FED4F957B4726AFC9A997F3623178C26" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apodanthaceae" genus="Pilostyles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulei">Pilostyles ulei</taxonomicName>
Solms-Laub., in Goebel, Organogr. Pfl. 2,1: 434. Figure 292 (1900), descr. in Endriss, Flora, 
<normalizedToken id="B859AB1FBD68848FBEA2567AAEAB7CEF" originalValue="Ergänz">Ergaenz</normalizedToken>
.-Bd. 91: 209. 1902. Type: Brazil, Goias, parasitic on 
<taxonomicName id="94B4D224F658DE7DD43BC2A5F913E601" genus="Fabaceae" lsidName="" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" rank="genus">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="17A22E78E0F27B68125A24B70CDCAA23" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">E. Ule s.n</emphasis>
. (B, destroyed in WWII; R has E. Ule 34, E. Ule 36, E. Ule 38, E. Ule 148, E. Ule 367, E. Ule 482, and E. Ule 483 labeled as this species, not seen). Comment: already 
<bibRefCitation id="CA913B4973B943CCBAAEADA30DE0705F" author="Solms-Laubach, H" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Biology and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="53" refId="B14" refString="Solms-Laubach, H, 1901. Rafflesiaceae. In: Engler A (Ed) Das Pflanzenreich IV. Engelmann, Leipzig, 75." title="Rafflesiaceae. In: Engler A (Ed) Das Pflanzenreich IV. Engelmann, Leipzig, 75." year="1901">Solms-Laubach (1901)</bibRefCitation>
and 
